    16‚Üí<div class="mdbook-version">
    17‚ÜíVersion: {{ mdbook-version }}
    18‚Üí</div>
    19‚Üí
    20‚Üí**mdBook** is a command line tool to create books with Markdown.
    21‚ÜíIt is ideal for creating product or API documentation, tutorials, course materials or anything that requires a clean,
    22‚Üíeasily navigable and customizable presentation.
    23‚Üí
    24‚Üí* Lightweight [Markdown] syntax helps you focus more on your content
    25‚Üí* Integrated [search] support
    26‚Üí* Color [syntax highlighting] for code blocks for many different languages
    27‚Üí* [Theme] files allow customizing the formatting of the output
    28‚Üí* [Preprocessors] can provide extensions for custom syntax and modifying content
    29‚Üí* [Backends] can render the output to multiple formats
    30‚Üí* Written in [Rust] for speed, safety, and simplicity
    31‚Üí* Automated testing of [Rust code samples]
    32‚Üí
    33‚ÜíThis guide is an example of what mdBook produces.
    34‚ÜímdBook is used by the Rust programming language project, and [The Rust Programming Language][trpl] book is another fine example of mdBook in action.
    35‚Üí
    36‚Üí[Markdown]: format/markdown.md
    37‚Üí[search]: guide/reading.md#search
    38‚Üí[syntax highlighting]: format/theme/syntax-highlighting.md
    39‚Üí[theme]: format/theme/index.html
    40‚Üí[preprocessors]: format/configuration/preprocessors.md
    41‚Üí[backends]: format/configuration/renderers.md
    42‚Üí[Rust]: https://www.rust-lang.org/
    43‚Üí[trpl]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/
